{
  "stem": "22889.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was very happy life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was on Saturday, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because during the week, we can't go to the Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I guess it was several different organization.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one tried to compete with each other, too-- like for instance, Betar was a difference, right-wing form of Zionist.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other were different.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I started, I remember, the Zionist organization was Akiba.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After a while, when I was growing up, when I was around eight, nine years old, 10 years old, I needed-- I needed more action.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's when I started to go to Betar.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Betar was more stronger organization.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They learn how to-- we were-- we were always taught, someday we have to liberate our country with force, not with money.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Again, like Akiba, [NON-ENGLISH] who spend the money, this to buy part of the country in Palestine, then.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And our leader was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was a leader from Betar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember, one time, you know, he came to our hometown and gave speech-- because he used to live in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's not too far.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We saw the brown shirt, dark brown with the blue handkerchiefs, here.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And everybody used to carry a stick-- this was our weapon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because many times we got into little problem with the Polish scouts, Boy Scouts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We used to fought with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They used to attack us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We used to protect ourselves with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because we live-- my town, where I live, was right in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "This was most beautiful part in Poland-- Nowy-Targ, Zakopane, right in the Carpathian mountain.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Shabbos afternoon, Shabbat, you know, we used to go, always, hiking in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we got into a lot of problems, sometimes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They used to throw stones at us, used to attack us.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
